[{"verseId":"brenton_1-kings_5_1","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":11,"bookName":"1 Kings","bookAbbrev":"1-kings","chapter":5,"verse":1,"text":"And thus the officers provided king Solomon: and every one in his month all the orders for the table of the king, they omit nothing. And they carried the barley and the straw for the horses and the chariots to the place where the king might be, each according to his charge.","searchKeywords":["and","thus","the","officers","provided","king","solomon","every","one","his","month","all","orders","for","table","they","omit","nothing","carried","barley","straw","horses","chariots","place","where","might","each","according","charge"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-kings_5_2","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":11,"bookName":"1 Kings","bookAbbrev":"1-kings","chapter":5,"verse":2,"text":"And these the requisite supplies for Solomon: in one day thirty measures of fine flour, and sixty measures of fine pounded meal,","searchKeywords":["and","these","the","requisite","supplies","for","solomon","one","day","thirty","measures","fine","flour","sixty","pounded","meal"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-kings_5_3","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":11,"bookName":"1 Kings","bookAbbrev":"1-kings","chapter":5,"verse":3,"text":"and ten choice calves, and twenty pastured oxen, and a hundred sheep, besides stags, and choice fatted does.","searchKeywords":["and","ten","choice","calves","twenty","pastured","oxen","hundred","sheep","besides","stags","fatted","does"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-kings_5_4","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":11,"bookName":"1 Kings","bookAbbrev":"1-kings","chapter":5,"verse":4,"text":"For he had dominion on this side the river, and he was at peace on all sides round about.","searchKeywords":["for","had","dominion","this","side","the","river","and","was","peace","all","sides","round","about"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-kings_5_9","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":11,"bookName":"1 Kings","bookAbbrev":"1-kings","chapter":5,"verse":9,"text":"And the Lord gave understanding to Solomon, and very much wisdom, and enlargement of heart, as the sand on the seashore.","searchKeywords":["and","the","lord","gave","understanding","solomon","very","much","wisdom","enlargement","heart","sand","seashore"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-kings_5_10","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":11,"bookName":"1 Kings","bookAbbrev":"1-kings","chapter":5,"verse":10,"text":"And Solomon abounded greatly beyond the wisdom of all the ancients, and beyond all the wise men of Egypt.","searchKeywords":["and","solomon","abounded","greatly","beyond","the","wisdom","all","ancients","wise","men","egypt"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-kings_5_11","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":11,"bookName":"1 Kings","bookAbbrev":"1-kings","chapter":5,"verse":11,"text":"And he was wiser than all men: and he was wiser than Gæthan the Zarite, and Ænan, and Chalcad and Darala the sons of Mal.","searchKeywords":["and","was","wiser","than","all","men","the","zarite","nan","chalcad","darala","sons","mal"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-kings_5_12","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":11,"bookName":"1 Kings","bookAbbrev":"1-kings","chapter":5,"verse":12,"text":"And Solomon spoke three thousand proverbs, and his songs were five thousand.","searchKeywords":["and","solomon","spoke","three","thousand","proverbs","his","songs","were","five"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-kings_5_13","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":11,"bookName":"1 Kings","bookAbbrev":"1-kings","chapter":5,"verse":13,"text":"And he spoke of trees, from the cedar in Libanus even to the hyssop which comes out through the wall: he spoke also of cattle, and of birds, and of reptiles, and of fishes.","searchKeywords":["and","spoke","trees","from","the","cedar","libanus","even","hyssop","which","comes","out","through","wall","also","cattle","birds","reptiles","fishes"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-kings_5_14","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":11,"bookName":"1 Kings","bookAbbrev":"1-kings","chapter":5,"verse":14,"text":"And all the nations came to hear the wisdom of Solomon, and from all the kings of the earth, as many as heard of his wisdom. And Solomon took to himself the daughter of Pharao to wife, and brought her into the city of David until he had finished the house of the Lord, and his own house, and the wall of Jerusalem.","searchKeywords":["and","all","the","nations","came","hear","wisdom","solomon","from","kings","earth","many","heard","his","took","himself","daughter","pharao","wife","brought","her","into","city","david","until","had","finished","house","lord","own","wall","jerusalem"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-kings_5_17","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":11,"bookName":"1 Kings","bookAbbrev":"1-kings","chapter":5,"verse":17,"text":"my father David, that he could not build a house to the name of the Lord my God because of the wars that compassed him about, until the Lord put them under the soles of his feet.","searchKeywords":["father","david","that","could","not","build","house","the","name","lord","god","because","wars","compassed","him","about","until","put","them","under","soles","his","feet"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-kings_5_18","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":11,"bookName":"1 Kings","bookAbbrev":"1-kings","chapter":5,"verse":18,"text":", and there is no evil trespass .","searchKeywords":["and","there","evil","trespass"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-kings_5_20","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":11,"bookName":"1 Kings","bookAbbrev":"1-kings","chapter":5,"verse":20,"text":"cut wood for me out of Libanus: and, behold, my servants with thy servants, and I will give thee the wages of thy service, according to all that thou shalt say, because thou knowest that we have no one skilled in cutting timber like the Sidonians.","searchKeywords":["cut","wood",